      "content": "I see. So it's basically saying they can come after me for things that aren't even my direct fault, just because they're \"connected\" to the work. It feels a bit like they're burying these risks in the middle of the text so you don't notice them until it's too late. Is there a way to describe these kinds of hidden, predatory legal developments? It feels like they're just waiting in the shadows for a mistake to happen.",
